main event: A civilian observed an unidentified object near Columbus, Ohio on July 10, 1966.
interesting points: The object appeared as a light and made a high-pitched sound.
The object moved in various directions, including east and west.
The sighting was within 3 miles of the University Airport (Don Scott Field), where the Air National Guard and civilians frequently operated aircraft.
The object was observed for approximately 10 minutes.
The witness estimated the object was around 5,000 feet up and moved at a fast speed, like a reciprocating engine aircraft.
